         <abstract>
            <p>In their enthusiasm for reducing pension contributions, many corporations are urging pension fund managers to invest in risky assets without, on one hand, providing assurance that pension beneficiaries will receive any rewards from risk taking. On the other hand, the same corporations often fail to protect the beneficiaries from possible investment losses.</p>
